de.bright_side.filesystemfacade.memoryfs

Class MemoryFSItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bright_side.filesystemfacade.memoryfs.MemoryFSItem

  • public class MemoryFSItem
extends Object
    contains the actual data and properties of the file while MemoryFile will be reading from this. It is required because it is possible to create a MemoryFile instance which does not exist in the FileSystem. Also there may be multiple MemoryFile instances which point to the same MemoryFSItem and the MemoryFSItem may change.
    Author:
    Philip Heyse
